source_code: Contains three photographs of the restauration of the Rubenshouse.
Annotation: Contains three photographs of the restauration of the Rubenshouse.

Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Spätzeit (Selbst)-Bildnisse" addressed (inside) to "Technische Hochschule Inst. F. Kunstgeschichte Darmstadt Hochschulstr."

- Notes about Rubens portraits
- First subfolder (Annotation: "Spaziergang"):
    - Notes, photos, an article and correspondence (dated 1941) about 'Rubens and his wife Helene Fourment in the garden' painting
-Notes about the portrait of Anthony Van Dyck.
- Second empty subfolder (Annotation: "Zu den Selbstbildnissen von Rubens")
- Third subfolder (Annotation: "Georg Petel Büste von Rubens 1633."):
    - Notes and correspondence (dated 1942) about Rubens bust by sculptor Georg Petel.  
  
Loose documentation reunited with the folder:   
     
- Small folder with photos of the Rubens House in Antwerp
- Photos of Rubens' bust
- Photo of a portrait
- Clear envelope (Annotation: "Rubenstoel") with 5 photos of Rubens' chair
- Photo of a medallion with two portrait in profile
